---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Support"
  description="Get support for Go Bananas. Contact info for testers, bug reports, feature requests, and feedback."
  path="/support"
>
  <section class="container-quiet page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Go Bananas</a></p>
    <h1 class="page-title">Support</h1>
    <p class="page-meta">Bug reports, feature requests, and beta access.</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="section-rule" />

  <article class="container-quiet section prose">
    <h2>How to reach us</h2>
    <p>
      Email{' '}
      <a href="mailto:feedback@bananascanner.com">feedback@bananascanner.com</a>{' '}
      for bug reports, feature requests, or anything else. Replies usually
      come within a few days.
    </p>
    <p>
      If it misreads a banana's ripeness, screenshot the result screen first.
      The diagnostic block at the bottom shows the hue values the classifier
      saw, which is the data we recalibrate from. Send that along with the
      stage you'd have called it.
    </p>

    <h2>Get the app</h2>
    <p>
      Go Bananas is out now, free, on the{' '}
      <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id6772261640">App Store</a>{' '}
      for iPhone and iPad and on{' '}
      <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.harnischllc.gobananas">Google Play</a>{' '}
      for Android.
    </p>

    <div class="screens screens-centered">
      <figure class="phone">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <img
            src="/screens/home-scan.png"
            alt="Go Bananas home screen with the Scan with camera button"
            width="600"
            height="1304"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="phone-cap">Scan with your camera</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="phone">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <img
            src="/screens/banana-bunch.png"
            alt="The Banana Bunch screen tracking named bananas and their ripeness"
            width="600"
            height="1304"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="phone-cap">Track your bunch</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="phone">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <img
            src="/screens/ripeness-scale.png"
            alt="The seven-stage USDA banana ripeness scale"
            width="600"
            height="1304"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="phone-cap">The 7-stage scale</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="phone">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <img
            src="/screens/rewards.png"
            alt="Rewards screen with the daily crate, streaks, and variety collection"
            width="600"
            height="1304"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="phone-cap">Daily crates and streaks</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <h2>Permissions and data</h2>
    <p>
      Everything runs on your device. Photos never leave your phone. See the{' '}
      <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-head {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
  }

  .page-meta {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section {
    padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }

  /* Keep the beta screenshot strip to a tidy two-up grid on wider screens
     (mobile still gets the horizontal scroll strip from the base .screens). */
  .screens {
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
</style>
